      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error (MAPE) of 4.7% for construct stiffness and 6.2% for yield load across N=11 specimens. 95% prediction interval of FEA ensemble contains 10 of 11 experimental observations. E-metric within acceptable range. Required level met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to device performance requirements and regulatory submission endpoints for Class II spinal implant.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary performance endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal pedicle screw systems. QoIs directly support 510(k) substantial equivalence demonstration. Required level met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
